# Example: Adding a New Feature

This example demonstrates adding a "Task Timer" feature to track time spent on tasks.

## 1. Create DocType

First, create the DocType for storing task time entries:

```bash
bench make-doctype "Task Timer"
```

Define fields in JSON:
```json
{
  "fields": [
    {
      "fieldname": "task",
      "fieldtype": "Link",
      "label": "Task",
      "options": "Task",
      "reqd": 1
    },
    {
      "fieldname": "start_time",
      "fieldtype": "Datetime",
      "label": "Start Time",
      "reqd": 1
    },
    {
      "fieldname": "end_time",
      "fieldtype": "Datetime",
      "label": "End Time"
    },
    {
      "fieldname": "duration",
      "fieldtype": "Duration",
      "label": "Duration",
      "read_only": 1
    }
  ]
}
```

